    "about_template": {
      "hero_overline": "Our story",
      "lab_overline": "The laboratory",
      "hero_overline_default": "Our story",
      "hero_heading_default": "Cultivating the extraordinary.",
      "hero_subheading_default": "South Africa's premier carnivorous plant and tissue culture nursery - field-tested protocols for collectors nationwide.",
      "split_overline_default": "A scientific history",
      "split_heading_default": "A scientific history of care",
      "split_text_default": "<p><strong>Bizarre Tropicals</strong> is South Africa's premier carnivorous plant and tissue culture nursery, meticulously curated by Jaco Van Den Berg. From tissue-cultured sundews to show-stopping Nepenthes, we grow and ship living specimens for collectors across the country.</p><p>Macro photography meets Southern Hemisphere culture notes on every genus page - light, water, substrate, humidity, dormancy, and feeding written for real benches and terrariums, not generic houseplant advice.</p><p>We propagate in-house, acclimate stock before shipping, and prioritize plants that arrive ready for your collection.</p>",
      "lab_overline_default": "The laboratory",
      "lab_heading_default": "Science in service of nature.",
      "lab_text_default": "<p>Tissue culture lets us multiply rare carnivorous plants under sterile conditions - preserving genetics without wild collection or poaching. Every flask in our lab is a living archive of species that might otherwise vanish from cultivation.</p><p>From initiation to weaning, we track each line for vigor, trueness to name, and pathogen-free growth before plants ever reach the bench. That is how Bizarre Tropicals supplies collectors with ethically propagated stock you can grow with confidence.</p>",
      "curator_heading_default": "A message from Jaco Van Den Berg.",
      "curator_text_default": "<p>I have spent years studying and growing carnivorous genera across South Africa - from windowsill Drosera to climate-controlled Nepenthes. What began as a collector's obsession became a nursery built on science, patience, and respect for these plants in the wild.</p><p>At Bizarre Tropicals, every species we list reflects hands-on culture: the humidity, the dormancy timing, the substrate that actually works on a Gauteng bench. If you are building a collection, I want you to succeed - not just make a purchase.</p>",
      "curator_signature_default": "Jaco Van Den Berg"
    },
