  "policies": {
    "contact_information_body": "<p><strong>Bizarre Tropicals</strong> is a South African specialist retailer of carnivorous plants and growing supplies.</p><ul><li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"mailto:info@bizarretropicals.co.za\">info@bizarretropicals.co.za</a></li><li><strong>Phone / WhatsApp:</strong> <a href=\"https://wa.me/27721527446\">+27 72 152 7446</a></li><li><strong>Address:</strong> 533 Andries Strydom Street, Pretoria, GP, 0010, South Africa (bench visits by appointment)</li><li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href=\"/pages/contact\">Contact page</a> for enquiries, availability, and shipping questions</li></ul><p>We respond to order and plant-health enquiries as quickly as possible. For transit damage, include your order number and photos within 48 hours of delivery.</p>",
    "refund_policy_body": "<p>Because we sell living carnivorous plants, we handle issues case by case with the health of the specimen as the priority. Please read this policy before ordering.</p><ul><li><strong>Transit damage:</strong> Contact us within 48 hours of delivery with clear photos of the plant and packaging. We will offer a replacement, credit, or refund where appropriate.</li><li><strong>Incorrect item:</strong> If we sent the wrong plant or size, notify us within 7 days and we will correct the order at no extra shipping cost where possible.</li><li><strong>Change of mind:</strong> Living plants cannot be returned once dispatched due to biosecurity and stress. Growing supplies in unopened resaleable condition may be eligible for return — contact us first.</li><li><strong>Cancellations:</strong> Orders may be cancelled before dispatch. After dispatch, standard transit rules apply.</li><li><strong>Refunds:</strong> Approved refunds are returned to the original payment method within 5–10 business days.</li><li><strong>How to reach us:</strong> Email <a href=\"mailto:info@bizarretropicals.co.za\">info@bizarretropicals.co.za</a>, WhatsApp <a href=\"https://wa.me/27721527446\">+27 72 152 7446</a>, or use our <a href=\"/pages/contact\">contact page</a>. Include your order number and photos for plant-health issues.</li></ul>",
    "shipping_policy_body": "<p>We ship living carnivorous plants nationwide using couriers experienced with temperature-sensitive freight. Orders are typically dispatched on <strong>Mondays</strong> to minimise weekend delays in transit.</p><ul><li><strong>Packaging:</strong> Specimens are secured in laboratory-grade sphagnum and climate-appropriate insulation. Pots are stabilised so traps and pitchers are not crushed in handling.</li><li><strong>Rates:</strong> Shipping is calculated at checkout based on destination, cart size, and courier service. All prices are in South African Rand (ZAR).</li><li><strong>Processing:</strong> We aim to dispatch within a few business days of payment. During peak season or extreme weather, dispatch may take longer — we will email you if your order is held.</li><li><strong>Receiving your parcel:</strong> Unbox as soon as practical. Photograph any damage to the plant and packaging before repotting. Acclimate the specimen to its growing environment gradually; avoid direct sun or fertiliser for the first week after transit.</li><li><strong>Live arrival:</strong> Report transit damage within <strong>48 hours</strong> with clear photos so we can assist under our <a href=\"/policies/refund-policy\">return and refund policy</a>.</li><li><strong>Hold for weather:</strong> We may delay dispatch during extreme heat or cold to protect living stock. We will contact you if your order is held.</li><li><strong>Remote &amp; PO boxes:</strong> Some lines are unsuitable for very long transits or locker delivery. Contact us before ordering rare or high-value specimens if you are unsure about your address.</li></ul><p>Questions before you order? Email <a href=\"mailto:info@bizarretropicals.co.za\">info@bizarretropicals.co.za</a>, WhatsApp <a href=\"https://wa.me/27721527446\">+27 72 152 7446</a>, or use our <a href=\"/pages/contact\">contact page</a>.</p>",
    "privacy_policy_body": "<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 28, 2026</p>\n\n<p><strong>Bizarre Tropicals</strong> operates this store and website, including all related information, content, features, tools, products and services, in order to provide you, the customer, with a curated shopping experience (the &ldquo;Services&rdquo;). Bizarre Tropicals is powered by Shopify, which enables us to provide the Services to you. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information when you visit, use, or make a purchase or other transaction using the Services or otherwise communicate with us. If there is a conflict between our <a href=\"/policies/terms-of-service\">Terms of Service</a> and this Privacy Policy, this Privacy Policy controls with respect to the collection, processing, and disclosure of your personal information.</p>\n\n<p>Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By using and accessing any of the Services, you acknowledge that you have read this Privacy Policy and understand the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.</p>\n\n<h2>Personal information we collect or process</h2>\n<p>When we use the term &ldquo;personal information,&rdquo; we are referring to information that identifies or can reasonably be linked to you or another person. Personal information does not include information that is collected anonymously or that has been de-identified, so that it cannot identify or be reasonably linked to you. We may collect or process the following categories of personal information, including inferences drawn from this personal information, depending on how you interact with the Services, where you live, and as permitted or required by applicable law:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Contact details</strong> including your name, address, billing address, shipping address, phone number, and email address.</li>\n  <li><strong>Financial information</strong> including credit card, debit card, and financial account numbers, payment card information, financial account information, transaction details, form of payment, payment confirmation and other payment details. Card data is processed by Shopify and payment partners — we do not store full card numbers on our servers.</li>\n  <li><strong>Account information</strong> including your username, password, security questions, preferences and settings.</li>\n  <li><strong>Transaction information</strong> including the items you view, put in your cart, add to your wishlist (if available), or purchase, return, exchange or cancel and your past transactions.</li>\n  <li><strong>Communications with us</strong> including the information you include in communications with us, for example, when sending a customer support inquiry (including photos you send for plant-health or transit-damage support).</li>\n  <li><strong>Device information</strong> including information about your device, browser, or network connection, your IP address, and other unique identifiers.</li>\n  <li><strong>Usage information</strong> including information regarding your interaction with the Services, including how and when you interact with or navigate the Services.</li>\n  <li><strong>Newsletter and marketing</strong> including your email address and communication preferences if you subscribe or opt in to marketing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Personal information sources</h2>\n<p>We may collect personal information from the following sources:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Directly from you</strong> including when you create an account, visit or use the Services, communicate with us, or otherwise provide us with your personal information;</li>\n  <li><strong>Automatically through the Services</strong> including from your device when you use our products or services or visit our websites, and through the use of cookies and similar technologies;</li>\n  <li><strong>From our service providers</strong> including when we engage them to enable certain technology and when they collect or process your personal information on our behalf;</li>\n  <li><strong>From our partners or other third parties</strong> where permitted by law and disclosed to you.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How we use your personal information</h2>\n<p>Depending on how you interact with us or which of the Services you use, we may use personal information for the following purposes:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Provide, tailor, and improve the Services.</strong> We use your personal information to provide you with the Services, including to perform our contract with you, to process your payments, to fulfil your orders, to remember your preferences and items you are interested in, to send notifications to you related to your account, to process purchases, returns, exchanges or other transactions, to create, maintain and otherwise manage your account, to arrange for shipping, to facilitate any returns and exchanges, to enable you to post reviews, and to create a customized shopping experience for you, such as recommending products related to your purchases. This may include using your personal information to better tailor and improve the Services.</li>\n  <li><strong>Marketing and advertising.</strong> We use your personal information for marketing and promotional purposes, such as to send marketing, advertising and promotional communications by email, text message or postal mail, and to show you online advertisements for products or services on the Services or other websites, including based on items you previously have purchased or added to your cart and other activity on the Services. We only send promotional marketing where you have opted in or as otherwise permitted by law.</li>\n  <li><strong>Security and fraud prevention.</strong> We use your personal information to authenticate your account, to provide a secure payment and shopping experience, detect, investigate or take action regarding possible fraudulent, illegal, unsafe, or malicious activity, protect public safety, and to secure our services. If you choose to use the Services and register an account, you are responsible for keeping your account credentials safe. We highly recommend that you do not share your username, password or other access details with anyone else.</li>\n  <li><strong>Communicating with you.</strong> We use your personal information to provide you with customer support, to be responsive to you, to provide effective services to you and to maintain our business relationship with you.</li>\n  <li><strong>Legal reasons.</strong> We use your personal information to comply with applicable law or respond to valid legal process, including requests from law enforcement or government agencies, to investigate or participate in civil discovery, potential or actual litigation, or other adversarial legal proceedings, and to enforce or investigate potential violations of our terms or policies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information to third parties for money. Where applicable law defines &ldquo;sell&rdquo; or &ldquo;share&rdquo; more broadly (including certain advertising activities), see <strong>How we disclose personal information</strong> below and your rights.</p>\n\n<h2>How we disclose personal information</h2>\n<p>In certain circumstances, we may disclose your personal information to third parties for legitimate purposes subject to this Privacy Policy. Such circumstances may include:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>With Shopify, vendors and other third parties who perform services on our behalf (e.g. IT management, payment processing, data analytics, customer support, cloud storage, fulfillment and shipping).</li>\n  <li>With business and marketing partners to provide marketing services and advertise to you. For example, we use Shopify to support personalized advertising with third-party services based on your online activity with different merchants and websites. Our business and marketing partners will use your information in accordance with their own privacy notices. Depending on where you reside, you may have a right to direct us not to share information about you to show you targeted advertisements and marketing based on your online activity with different merchants and websites.</li>\n  <li>With couriers and logistics providers to deliver your orders (name, phone, and delivery address).</li>\n  <li>When you direct, request us or otherwise consent to our disclosure of certain information to third parties, such as to ship you products or through your use of social media widgets or login integrations.</li>\n  <li>With our affiliates or otherwise within our corporate group.</li>\n  <li>In connection with a business transaction such as a merger or bankruptcy, to comply with any applicable legal obligations (including to respond to subpoenas, search warrants and similar requests), to enforce any applicable terms of service or policies, and to protect or defend the Services, our rights, and the rights of our users or others.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>\n<p>The site uses cookies and similar technologies for essential functions (cart, checkout, security), preferences, and analytics. You can manage non-essential cookies via Shopify&rsquo;s cookie banner where shown. Blocking essential cookies may affect checkout. For more information, see <strong>Relationship with Shopify</strong> below and Shopify&rsquo;s cookie disclosures.</p>\n\n<h2>Relationship with Shopify</h2>\n<p>The Services are hosted by Shopify, which collects and processes personal information about your access to and use of the Services in order to provide and improve the Services for you. Information you submit to the Services will be transmitted to and shared with Shopify as well as third parties that may be located in countries other than where you reside, in order to provide and improve the Services for you. In addition, to help protect, grow, and improve our business, we use certain Shopify enhanced features that incorporate data and information obtained from your interactions with our Store, along with other merchants and with Shopify. To provide these enhanced features, Shopify may make use of personal information collected about your interactions with our store, along with other merchants, and with Shopify. In these circumstances, Shopify is responsible for the processing of your personal information, including for responding to your requests to exercise your rights over use of your personal information for these purposes. To learn more about how Shopify uses your personal information and any rights you may have, you can visit the <a href=\"https://www.shopify.com/legal/privacy/app-users\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Shopify Consumer Privacy Policy</a>. Depending on where you live, you may exercise certain rights with respect to your personal information at the <a href=\"https://privacy.shopify.com/en\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Shopify Privacy Portal</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Third-party websites and links</h2>\n<p>The Services may provide links to websites or other online platforms operated by third parties. If you follow links to sites not affiliated or controlled by us, you should review their privacy and security policies and other terms and conditions. We do not guarantee and are not responsible for the privacy or security of such sites, including the accuracy, completeness, or reliability of information found on these sites. Information you provide on public or semi-public venues, including information you share on third-party social networking platforms may also be viewable by other users of the Services and/or users of those third-party platforms without limitation as to its use by us or by a third party. Our inclusion of such links does not, by itself, imply any endorsement of the content on such platforms or of their owners or operators, except as disclosed on the Services.</p>\n\n<h2>Children&rsquo;s data</h2>\n<p>The Services are not intended to be used by children, and we do not knowingly collect any personal information about children under the age of majority in your jurisdiction. If you are the parent or guardian of a child who has provided us with their personal information, you may contact us using the contact details set out below to request that it be deleted. As of the date of this Privacy Policy, we do not have actual knowledge that we &ldquo;share&rdquo; or &ldquo;sell&rdquo; (as those terms are defined in applicable law) personal information of individuals under 16 years of age.</p>\n\n<h2>Security and retention of your information</h2>\n<p>Please be aware that no security measures are perfect or impenetrable, and we cannot guarantee &ldquo;perfect security.&rdquo; In addition, any information you send to us may not be secure while in transit. We recommend that you do not use unsecure channels to communicate sensitive or confidential information to us, and that you use a strong password if you create a customer account.</p>\n<p>How long we retain your personal information depends on different factors, such as whether we need the information to maintain your account, to provide you with Services, comply with legal obligations (including South African tax and record-keeping requirements), resolve disputes or enforce other applicable contracts and policies. Marketing data is retained until you unsubscribe or request deletion, subject to legal holds.</p>\n\n<h2>Your rights and choices</h2>\n<p>Depending on where you live, you may have some or all of the rights listed below in relation to your personal information. However, these rights are not absolute, may apply only in certain circumstances and, in certain cases, we may decline your request as permitted by law.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Right to access / know.</strong> You may have a right to request access to personal information that we hold about you.</li>\n  <li><strong>Right to delete.</strong> You may have a right to request that we delete personal information we maintain about you.</li>\n  <li><strong>Right to correct.</strong> You may have a right to request that we correct inaccurate personal information we maintain about you.</li>\n  <li><strong>Right of portability.</strong> You may have a right to receive a copy of the personal information we hold about you and to request that we transfer it to a third party, in certain circumstances and with certain exceptions.</li>\n  <li><strong>Managing communication preferences.</strong> We may send you promotional emails, and you may opt out of receiving these at any time by using the unsubscribe option displayed in our emails to you. If you opt out, we may still send you non-promotional emails, such as those about your account or orders that you have made.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You may exercise any of these rights where indicated on the Services or by contacting us using the contact details provided below. To learn more about how Shopify uses your personal information and any rights you may have, including rights related to data processed by Shopify, visit the <a href=\"https://privacy.shopify.com/en\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Shopify Privacy Portal</a>.</p>\n<p>We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of these rights. We may need to verify your identity before we can process your requests, as permitted or required under applicable law. In accordance with applicable laws, you may designate an authorized agent to make requests on your behalf to exercise your rights. Before accepting such a request from an agent, we will require that the agent provide proof you have authorized them to act on your behalf, and we may need you to verify your identity directly with us. We will respond to your request in a timely manner as required under applicable law.</p>\n\n<h2>South Africa (POPIA)</h2>\n<p>If you are in the Republic of South Africa, the Protection of Personal Information Act, 2013 (POPIA) may apply. You may have the right to access, correct, delete, or object to certain processing of your personal information, and to lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator (South Africa). We process personal information lawfully and for purposes you would reasonably expect when you shop with us or contact us. To exercise POPIA-related rights, contact us below. We may need to verify your identity before responding.</p>\n\n<h2>Complaints</h2>\n<p>If you have complaints about how we process your personal information, please contact us using the contact details provided below. Depending on where you live, you may have the right to appeal our decision by contacting us using the contact details set out below, or lodge your complaint with your local data protection authority (in South Africa, the Information Regulator).</p>\n\n<h2>International transfers</h2>\n<p>Please note that we may transfer, store and process your personal information outside the country you live in, including through Shopify and service providers in other countries.</p>\n<p>If we transfer your personal information out of the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, we will rely on recognized transfer mechanisms like the European Commission&rsquo;s Standard Contractual Clauses, or any equivalent contracts issued by the relevant competent authority of the UK, as relevant, unless the data transfer is to a country that has been determined to provide an adequate level of protection.</p>\n\n<h2>Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>\n<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time, including to reflect changes to our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will post the revised Privacy Policy on this website, update the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date and provide notice as required by applicable law. Continued use of the Services after changes means you accept the updated policy, subject to applicable law.</p>\n\n<h2>Contact</h2>\n<p>Should you have any questions about our privacy practices or this Privacy Policy, or if you would like to exercise any of the rights available to you, please contact us:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"mailto:info@bizarretropicals.co.za\">info@bizarretropicals.co.za</a></li>\n  <li><strong>Phone / WhatsApp:</strong> <a href=\"https://wa.me/27721527446\">+27 72 152 7446</a></li>\n  <li><strong>Postal address:</strong> 533 Andries Strydom Street, Pretoria, GP, 0010, South Africa</li>\n  <li><strong>Online:</strong> <a href=\"/pages/contact\">Contact page</a></li>\n</ul>",
    "terms_of_service_body": "<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 28, 2026</p>\n\n<p>Welcome to <strong>Bizarre Tropicals</strong>. These Terms of Service (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern your access to and use of our website, online store, and related services (collectively, the &ldquo;Services&rdquo;). By visiting the Services or placing an order, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Services.</p>\n\n<p>These Terms work together with our <a href=\"/policies/privacy-policy\">Privacy Policy</a>, <a href=\"/policies/shipping-policy\">Shipping policy</a>, and <a href=\"/policies/refund-policy\">Return and refund policy</a>. If there is a conflict between these Terms and another policy about privacy or personal information, the Privacy Policy controls for that subject matter.</p>\n\n<h2>1. Who we are</h2>\n<p>The Services are operated by <strong>Bizarre Tropicals</strong>, a South African retailer of carnivorous plants and growing supplies. Our contact details are at the end of these Terms.</p>\n<p>The Services are hosted on Shopify, which provides e-commerce, checkout, and related infrastructure.</p>\n\n<h2>2. Eligibility</h2>\n<p>You must be able to form a binding contract under applicable law to use the Services and place orders. By using the Services, you represent that the information you provide is accurate and that you are authorised to use any payment method you submit.</p>\n\n<h2>3. Accounts</h2>\n<p>If you create a customer account, you are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your login credentials and for all activity under your account. Notify us promptly if you suspect unauthorised access. We may suspend or close accounts that violate these Terms or pose a security risk.</p>\n\n<h2>4. Products and listings</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>We sell living carnivorous plants and related growing supplies. Descriptions, photographs, metafields (including botanical names, difficulty, and care notes), and availability are provided in good faith but may change without notice.</li>\n  <li>Living plants are natural products — size, colour, pitcher or trap development, and vigour may vary from photos. We do not guarantee identical appearance to catalogue images.</li>\n  <li>Some species or cultivars may be subject to availability, season, or regulatory restrictions (including CITES where applicable). We sell for domestic use in South Africa unless we expressly agree otherwise in writing.</li>\n  <li>Care information on genus pages and product pages is educational and does not guarantee growing success in your conditions. You are responsible for suitable light, water, soil, temperature, and compliance with local rules.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>5. Prices, taxes, and payment</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>All prices are shown in <strong>South African Rand (ZAR)</strong> unless stated otherwise.</li>\n  <li>Prices, shipping charges, and promotions may change before checkout is completed. The price charged is the price shown at checkout when you submit payment.</li>\n  <li>Payment is processed through Shopify and approved payment providers. You authorise us and our processors to charge your selected payment method for your order total.</li>\n  <li>We may refuse or cancel orders (for example: stock errors, pricing mistakes, suspected fraud, or restrictions on certain products). If we cancel after payment, we will refund amounts paid for the cancelled items.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>6. Orders and contract</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Your order is an offer to purchase. A binding contract is formed when we send an order confirmation email (or otherwise confirm acceptance). We may accept part of an order and cancel unavailable items with a refund.</li>\n  <li>You are responsible for accurate shipping and contact details. Delays or loss caused by incorrect addresses or failure to receive the parcel may affect remedies available under our <a href=\"/policies/refund-policy\">Return and refund policy</a>.</li>\n  <li>We may limit quantities per customer, per order, or per household where reasonably necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>7. Shipping and delivery</h2>\n<p>Shipping terms, dispatch timing, packaging, and live-plant handling are described in our <a href=\"/policies/shipping-policy\">Shipping policy</a>. Risk of loss for goods generally passes to you upon delivery to the address you provide, subject to applicable law and our refund policy for qualifying transit damage.</p>\n\n<h2>8. Returns, refunds, and cancellations</h2>\n<p>Returns, replacements, refunds, and cancellations are governed by our <a href=\"/policies/refund-policy\">Return and refund policy</a>. Living plants generally cannot be returned after dispatch due to biosecurity and plant stress; contact us promptly if there is transit damage or an fulfilment error.</p>\n\n<h2>9. Acceptable use</h2>\n<p>You agree not to:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Use the Services unlawfully or in a way that harms us, other customers, or third parties;</li>\n  <li>Attempt to interfere with the security or operation of the Services (including scraping, malware, or unauthorised access);</li>\n  <li>Misrepresent your identity or payment authority;</li>\n  <li>Resell or export products in breach of law or our policies without written permission.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>10. Intellectual property</h2>\n<p>All content on the Services — including text, graphics, logos, photographs, and layout — is owned by Bizarre Tropicals or used under licence and is protected by copyright and other intellectual property laws. You may not copy, reproduce, or exploit our content for commercial purposes without our prior written consent, except as allowed by law or for personal, non-commercial reference.</p>\n\n<h2>11. Third-party links and services</h2>\n<p>The Services may link to third-party websites or tools (for example social media). We are not responsible for third-party content, policies, or practices. Your use of third-party services is at your own risk.</p>\n\n<h2>12. Disclaimers</h2>\n<p>To the fullest extent permitted by South African law, the Services and all products are provided on an &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available&rdquo; basis. We disclaim warranties not required by law, including implied warranties of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose, except where they cannot be excluded.</p>\n<p>We do not warrant uninterrupted or error-free operation of the Services. Growing outcomes depend on your care and environment; we are not liable for plant loss after delivery except as set out in our refund policy.</p>\n\n<h2>13. Limitation of liability</h2>\n<p>To the extent permitted by law:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>We are not liable for indirect, incidental, special, or consequential loss (including lost profits or data) arising from your use of the Services or products.</li>\n  <li>Our total liability for any claim relating to an order is limited to the amount you paid for the products giving rise to the claim, except where law requires otherwise (for example gross negligence or liability that cannot be limited).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Nothing in these Terms limits rights you may have under the South African Consumer Protection Act or other mandatory consumer laws where they apply to you.</p>\n\n<h2>14. Indemnity</h2>\n<p>You agree to indemnify and hold us harmless from claims, losses, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees) arising from your breach of these Terms, misuse of the Services, or violation of law, except to the extent caused by our wrongful conduct.</p>\n\n<h2>15. Governing law and disputes</h2>\n<p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the <strong>Republic of South Africa</strong>. You agree to the exclusive jurisdiction of the South African courts, subject to any mandatory rights you have to bring proceedings in another forum under applicable consumer law.</p>\n<p>Before formal proceedings, we encourage you to contact us so we can try to resolve concerns in good faith.</p>\n\n<h2>16. Changes to these Terms</h2>\n<p>We may update these Terms from time to time. The &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date above indicates the current version. Material changes may be communicated as required by law. Continued use of the Services after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms, subject to applicable law.</p>\n\n<h2>17. Contact</h2>\n<p>Questions about these Terms:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"mailto:info@bizarretropicals.co.za\">info@bizarretropicals.co.za</a></li>\n  <li><strong>Phone / WhatsApp:</strong> <a href=\"https://wa.me/27721527446\">+27 72 152 7446</a></li>\n  <li><strong>Postal address:</strong> 533 Andries Strydom Street, Pretoria, GP, 0010, South Africa</li>\n  <li><strong>Online:</strong> <a href=\"/pages/contact\">Contact page</a></li>\n</ul>",
    "legal_notice_body": "<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 28, 2026</p>\n\n<p>This Legal Notice provides identifying and regulatory information about the operator of the Bizarre Tropicals online store and website (the &ldquo;Services&rdquo;). It is provided for transparency and to meet common e-commerce disclosure expectations. It should be read together with our <a href=\"/policies/terms-of-service\">Terms of Service</a> and <a href=\"/policies/privacy-policy\">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Website operator</h2>\n<p><strong>Trading name:</strong> Bizarre Tropicals<br>\n<strong>Nature of business:</strong> Retail sale of carnivorous plants and related growing supplies (online store)<br>\n<strong>Country of operation:</strong> Republic of South Africa</p>\n\n<h2>Contact details</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"mailto:info@bizarretropicals.co.za\">info@bizarretropicals.co.za</a></li>\n  <li><strong>Phone / WhatsApp:</strong> <a href=\"https://wa.me/27721527446\">+27 72 152 7446</a></li>\n  <li><strong>Physical address:</strong> 533 Andries Strydom Street, Pretoria, GP, 0010, South Africa</li>\n  <li><strong>Customer enquiries:</strong> <a href=\"/pages/contact\">Contact page</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Bench visits and collection appointments are by arrangement unless otherwise stated on the contact page.</p>\n\n<h2>Platform and payments</h2>\n<p>The Services are hosted and powered by <strong>Shopify Inc.</strong> and its affiliates, which provide the online store, checkout, and related e-commerce infrastructure. Payment processing is handled by Shopify and approved payment partners. Card and payment data are processed according to our Privacy Policy and the payment providers&rsquo; terms — we do not store full payment card numbers on our own servers.</p>\n<p>Shopify&apos;s corporate information and policies are available at <a href=\"https://www.shopify.com/legal\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">shopify.com/legal</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Company registration and